write_instance_obs(25.10)                            write_instance_obs(25.10)

Name
       write_instance_obs  -  Saves all the instance obstruction shapes of the
       specified layer in an output file

Syntax
       write_instance_obs

       [-help]

       <output_file>[-layer <layer_name>]

       [-with_outer_shape]

       Saves all the instance obstruction shapes of the specified layer in  an
       output file.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each write_instance_obs parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man write_instance_obs

       <output_file>
              Specifies  the name of the output file in which the instance ob-
              struction shapes of the specified layer will be saved.

       -layer <layer_name>
              Specifies the name  of  the  layer  whose  instance  obstruction
              shapes will be saved in the output file.

       -with_outer_shape
              Saves  the  OBS shape within and outside the inst boundary. When
              this parameter is not used, the software  saves  the  OBS  shape
              only within the inst boundary.

              See the example below:

              * When  the  -with_outer_shape  parameter  is  not used, the OBS
                shape within the inst boundary is saved, as highlighted in the
                red rectangle in the figure shown below:

              * When the -with_outer_shape parameter  is  used,  complete  OBS
                shape,  within  and  outside  the  inst boundary, is saved, as
                highlighted in the red rectangle in the figure shown below:

